First, ensure you have a C compiler installed on your system. Popular choices include GCC (part of the MinGW or Cygwin packages for Windows) or the macOS and Linux built-in compilers.

### Step 2: Choose a Graphics Library
For simple text-based games like the snake game, you can use the standard C library functions for text output. However, if you want to use images, you might consider using a graphics library like SDL (Simple DirectMedia Layer) or Allegro. For this guide, we'll use SDL, which is more powerful and flexible.

